beer.beer_description: A Sierra Nevada recipe brewed by over 1,000 breweries nationwide in the name of a good cause. All proceeds from the sale of this beer are going to those impacted by the Camp Fire disaster in Butte County, CA. This IPA is brewed with Crystal malt and hopped with Centennial and Cascade hops. Red-orange in color with pleasant citrus and floral hop characteristics, this is the closest thing you’ll ever find to a Sierra beer in Founders. Enjoy and cheers to helping out fellow brewers!
